
Requirements:
  - hadoop-0.20.1 (libhdfs.so, hadoop-0.20.1-core.jar, commons-logging-1.0.4.jar)
     http://hadoop.apache.org/hdfs/
    
  - sun-java6-jdk  (libjvm.so)
     # apt-get install sun-java6-jdk

 The files used by libpyhdfs can be found at:
  - libjvm.so (/usr/lib/jvm/java-6-sun/jre/lib/i386/server/libjvm.so)
  - libhdfs.so (symbolic link to `libhdfs.so.0')
  - libhdfs.so.0 ($HADOOPHOME/c++/[Linux-i386-32 | Linux-amd64-64]/lib)
  - commons-logging-x.x.x.jar ($HADOOPHOME)
  - hadoop-x.x.x-core.jar ($HADOOPHOME)

Setting CLASSPATH:
 $ export CLASSPATH=/path/to/hadoop-x.x.x-core.jar:/path/to/commons-loggin-x.x.x.jar
